   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR GOD'S SPIRIT OF LIFE BECOMING THE WAY FOR THE PRIESTS OF THE GOSPEL TO BEGET, NOURISH, TEACH, AND BUILD Scripture Reading: 1 Pet 1:2b; John 3:5-6; 1 Cor 10:3-4; Rom 15:16; Eph 4:12; 1 Cor 14:1, 3-5, 12, 31; 12:8 OUTLINE We, by God's Spirit of life, causing the sinners to be sanctified and regenerated: God's Spirit of life first sanctifying the sinners 1 Pet 1:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God's Spirit of life next regenerating the sanctified sinners John 3:5-6.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>We, with God's Spirit of life as food and drink, feeding the regenerated believers and giving them to drink 1 Cor 10:3-4: God's Spirit of life as food being the pneumatic Christ as our food.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>God's Spirit of life as drink being also the pneumatic Christ as our drink.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>We, through God's Spirit of life, sanctifying and perfecting the saints, that they may do the work of the building up of the Body of Christ Rom 15:16; Eph 4:12: Teaching and sanctifying.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Unto the perfecting.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>We, by God's Spirit of life, helping the saints to prophesy for the Lord, unto the building up of the church as the Body of Christ 1 Cor 14:1, 3-5, 12, 31: To prophesy for the Lord, there being the need for the spiritual words.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The spiritual words coming from God's Spirit of life 1 Cor 12:8.</S>
   </TEXT>
